    { "element": "h2", "children": "üìê 1. What Is a Linear System?" },
    {
        "element": "p",
        "children": "A **system of linear equations** is a collection of two or more linear equations involving the same set of variables."
    },
    { "element": "h3", "children": "Example (2√ó2 System):" },
    {
        "element": "mathjax",
        "children": "\\begin{align*} (1)&\\quad 2x + y &= 5 \\\\ (2)&\\quad x - y &= 1 \\end{align*}"
    },
    {
        "element": "p",
        "children": "We seek values of **$x$** and **$y$** that satisfy **both equations simultaneously**."
    },
    {
        "element": "q",
        "children": "‚úÖ A **solution** to a linear system is an assignment of values to the variables that makes **all equations true** at once."
    },
    { "element": "hr" },
    { "element": "h2", "children": "üßÆ 2. Solving a System Algebraically" },
    {
        "element": "p",
        "children": "Let‚Äôs solve the above system using **substitution** or **elimination**."
    },
    { "element": "h3", "children": "Using Elimination:" },
    { "element": "p", "children": "Add equations (1) and (2):" },
    {
        "element": "mathjax",
        "children": "(2x + y) + (x - y) = 5 + 1 \\Rightarrow 3x = 6 \\Rightarrow x = 2"
    },
    { "element": "p", "children": "Plug **$x = 2$** into equation (2):" },
    { "element": "mathjax", "children": "2 - y = 1 \\Rightarrow y = 1" },
    { "element": "q", "children": "‚úÖ Solution: **$(x, y) = (2, 1)$**" },
    {
        "element": "p",
        "children": "This is the **only pair** that satisfies both equations."
    },
